Help: This is an RPN calculator. Press your first operand, then 'Enter', then your second Operand, then your Operator.
The stack is of infinite size - previous values may be accessed through the 'R↓' button, but I'd avoid it if I were you - as I say, it can be infinitely long.
The X Register is the contents of the screen, and the Y register is the last 'Entered' value. These are swapable through the 'X↔Y' button.
